PageTitle: protocol inbound ssh port 830 (NETCONF user interface view)
FuncDef:
The protocol inbound ssh port 830 command configures well-known port 830 to establish an SNETCONF connection.
The undo protocol inbound ssh port 830 command restores the default setting. The protocol inbound ssh port 830 command configures well-known port 830 to establish an SNETCONF connection. The undo protocol inbound ssh port 830 command restores the default setting. By default, SNETCONF connections are established using well-known port 22.
CLIs: undo protocol inbound ssh ipv4 port 830
undo protocol inbound ssh ipv6 port 830
ExtraInfo: You can run this command to set the SNETCONF port number to 830.
